column1: #Text=Bush urges US allies in Middle East to support Israeli-Palestinian peace talks
#Text=President Bush travels to the Middle East in the coming week in hopes of urging U.S. allies in the region to support Israeli-Palestinian peace talks

#Text=The president 's first stop is Israel where he says he will encourage Prime Minister Ehud Olmert and Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas to move forward with peace talks they began in November in the United States .

#Text= We will support democrats and reformers from Beirut and Baghdad to Damascus and Tehran , " said Mr. Bush .

column1: #Text=" We will stand with all those working to build a future of liberty and justice and peace . "
#Text=Analysts and activists in some Middle Eastern countries allied with the United States say 2007 was marked by governments backtracking from steps toward democracy .
#Text=During his trip , President Bush will meet with U.S. officials from Iraq for an update on the fighting there .
#Text=Public opinion polls say a majority of Americans believe the president 's decision to invade Iraq was a mistake .
#Text=And the deployment of more than 100,000 U.S. troops there is a major issue in this year 's presidential campaign .
#Text=In the Democratic radio address , party chairman Howard Dean urged American voters to put an end to seven years of Republican rule .
